overview: The user initiated a review of their sleep questionnaire application,
  which aims to provide interactive patient assessments and generate
  personalized reports. The assistant conducted a detailed analysis against the
  provided Statement of Work and questionnaire specification, identifying
  several critical gaps. High-priority missing features included a 1-10
  tiredness severity scale with safety warnings, explicit detection for COMISA
  and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and the inclusion of outbound links in the
  reports. The assistant has begun implementing these changes, starting with the
  tiredness severity scale, updating relevant types, validations, and UI
  components to incorporate this new functionality and its associated safety
  messaging.
